Ensuring maintenance-free import process for external CMSs.

They will be performed:

* {color:#14892c}Documentation (rules and restrictions) - will be prepared documentation rules of imports and the restrictions imposed by the repository pulse, and which significantly affect the import process (done){color}

* {color:#14892c}Inventory imported packages - Data transferred by the supplier will be postponed to a dedicated database, which will facilitate further operations on them, and help in solving potential problems and failures. (done){color}

* {color:#14892c}Error messages - cataloged, categorized and described will be all the errors in the import process so that the supplier can not properly react (done){color}

* {color:#14892c}Optimize import images - in one import, upload the same photo is done only once, regardless of the errors in the import of the remaining (done){color}

* {color:#14892c} Server Side Throttling - speed imports from individual suppliers will be able to be independently controlled, so as to ensure the stability of the platform in accordance with its current performance (done){color}

* {color:#14892c} New Import API - Prepared is a new Import API, allowing to simplify the whole process from the perspective of the supplier (done).{color}

* {color:#14892c}Takeover publication system from CMS Team and analysis New Repo API (done){color}

